&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Error 0x800F081F Windows 11/10 — Source Files Not Found Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/0x800f081f/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/0x800f081f/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-error-0x800f081f-windows-1110--source-files-not-found-fix"&gt;[Solution] Error 0x800F081F Windows 11/10 — Source Files Not Found Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Error 0x800F081F occurs when Windows cannot find the source files required to install a feature, most commonly the .NET Framework 3.5. It affects both Windows 10 and 11 when enabling legacy features.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error typically blocks installation of .NET Framework 3.5, which many older applications and games require. The fix involves pointing Windows to valid installation media or enabling the feature through alternative methods.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>